				<p>
				<h3>Who am I?</h3>
				I am Debsankha Manik, an undergraduate student majoring in physics at <a href="http://www.iiserkol.ac.in"><abbr title="Indian Institute of Science Education and Research">IISER</abbr> Kolkata</a> in West Bengal, India. Besides physics - my primary area of academic interest, I derive pleasure from dabbling in quite a few other subjects including mathematics, programming, electronics, literature and history. I am a firm believer in free and open source software, especially GNU/Linux.
				</p>
				<h3>What's in this site?</h3>
				<p>
				Various projects I have undertaken so far in the course of my undergraduate study are listed in the <a href='/projects'>Projects</a> page. In case of projects involving simulations or some other kind of programming, the programs can also be found there. Most of those codes are also hosted in this <a href="http://github.com/debsankha/bedtime-programming">public github repository</a>. All of them are licensed under GNU GPLv3, so if you want to use or modify them (I can't foresee why would you be tempted, though!), you are welcome to do so provided you comply with the terms of the aforementioned license.
				</p>
				<p>Sometimes when my boredom with the everyday chores reaches a threshold level (or sometimes out of real necessity), I set out to do some arbitrary tasks (like creating this website) which do not always reach completion. Some of those informal <i>'projects'</i>, if you would call them so, find their place of glory in the <a href='/junk'>Junk</a> page, among some other stuff. Most of these codes are scattered across my <a href="http://github.com/debsankha">github repositories</a>, too.
				</p>
				<p>
				The <a href='/stats'>Stat</a> page displays some stats about either me or this website. The stats are generally updated by me using my IM client or a nautilus action, utilizing the 'Incoming XMPP Messages' service of appengine.
				</p>
